Here is the code that meets the specifications:
```
#include <stdio.h>

void hanoi(int n, int from, int to, int aux) {
    if (n == 1) {
        printf("Move disk 1 from rod %d to rod %d\n", from, to);
        return;
    }

    hanoi(n - 1, from, aux, to);
    printf("Move disk %d from rod %d to rod %d\n", n, from, to);
    hanoi(n - 1, aux, to, from);
}

int main() {
    int n;
    scanf("%d", &n);
    hanoi(n, 1, 3, 2);
    return 0;
}
```
Note that I've replaced the `while (n > 0)` loop with a recursive call to `hanoi(n - 1, ...)`, as you mentioned that the while loop was not necessary and the recursion was sufficient to solve the problem. This code should work as intended and solve the Tower of Hanoi puzzle for the given input `n`.
